  [1mProject Overview â€“ terminalcp[22m

  terminalcp is a Node-JS library and CLI that lets AI agents (or any
  program) control interactive command-line tools just like a human would.
  It provides a play-wright-style interface for terminal programs, allowing
   them to be started, fed input, and have their output read in real-time.

  [2mCore Capabilities[22m

  â€¢ Spawn & control any CLI (debuggers, REPLs, build tools, etc.) in a
  pseudo-TTY.
  â€¢ Two output modes
  â€¢ Terminal mode (stdout) â€“ full rendered screen (useful for TUIs,
  debuggers).
  â€¢ Stream mode â€“ raw incremental output (good for logs, builds).
  â€¢ Send keystrokes (text, arrows, Ctrl-C, etc.) via escape-sequence
  strings.
  â€¢ Run multiple processes concurrently without blocking the agent.
  â€¢ Attach from a real terminal (like screen/tmux) to watch or intervene in
   AI-spawned sessions.

  [2mArchitecture[22m

  1. TerminalManager â€“ core library that creates PTY processes (via
  node-pty), emulates a terminal (using xterm.js headless), and handles
  I/O.
  2. TerminalServer â€“ a persistent background process that holds all
  sessions and listens on a Unix-domain socket.
  3. TerminalClient â€“ used by both the CLI and the MCP server to talk to
  the server.
  4. User Interfaces
  â€¢ MCP Server â€“ exposes a single terminalcp tool that receives JSON
  commands (start, stdin, stdout, stream, stop, etc.).
  â€¢ CLI â€“ a command-line wrapper (terminalcp start â€¦, terminalcp attach â€¦,
  etc.) that uses the same client.

  [2mTypical Use-Cases[22m

  â€¢ Debugging: drive LLDB/GDB, Python pdb, etc., step-by-step.
  â€¢ AI-to-AI collaboration: run Claude, Gemini, etc., as subprocesses.
  â€¢ REPL / shell automation: interact with Python, Node, Ruby REPLs.
  â€¢ TUI testing: automate Vim, htop, or any curses-based UI.
  â€¢ Log/Build monitoring: stream build output, watch logs, get only new
  output.
  â€¢ User attachment: users can attach to AI-spawned sessions via terminalcp
   attach .

  [2mHow to Use[22m

  â€¢ MCP: send JSON actions (start, stdin, stdout, stream, stop, etc.) to
  the server.
  â€¢ CLI: terminalcp start my-app "npm run dev"; terminalcp stdin my-app
  "echo hello" ::Enter; terminalcp stdout my-app; terminalcp attach my-app,
   etc.

  [2mDevelopment[22m

  â€¢ Install with Node 20+ (npm install), run tests (npm test), or use the
  CLI directly (npx tsx src/index.ts â€¦).

  [1mIn short: terminalcp provides a programmable, persistent [22m
  [1mterminal-emulation layer that lets AI agents (or any code) spawn, [22m
  [1mcontrol, and monitor interactive CLI tools as if a human were typing, [22m
  [1mwith both a programmatic API and a convenient CLI.[22m
